		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Dec 15th 12:44 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=13&mid=107133910350226&post=1&replyto=1071510265407766231"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1071510265407766231></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=287139"><span id=>thestraight</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />2 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=thestraight&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>The best thing to do is to not worry about doing dmg of any kind. Leave that to the tanks and nukers in your group and allow yourself to be their best friend by controlling the action that goes on in the battle.&nbsp;&nbsp;The damage dealing devices that chanters get are not up to par with the rest of the Norrathian body.  When you have room for them in your gem list its good to have them ready just in case, but this wont be the case for you for long.  Youll want to replace your direct damage, your DoT and your Blind spell. Charm can be very effective if used correctly...but you will have to decide how well you utilize it to see if you want to spend a slot on it.  Otherwise your best bet is to go with:<br>1)Tash<br>2)Slow<br>3)Mez<br>4)Group Mez<br>5)Root<br>6)Weaken<br>7)Stun<br>8)Stun<br><br>If you are practiced at your art, this line up should allow you to handle any situation your group comes upon.  <br>When buffing the group, ditch slow and weaken and keep the rest available so you can deal with an unplanned attack if one should arise.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
