		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kanador&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Nowadays, this is a whole lot easier.<br><br>You know how you can click on the little red spell book below to open up your spellbook to switch/load a spell gem?&nbsp;&nbsp;Next time, instead of left clicking that little sucker, right click it!<br><br>New menu under that button.....<br>     Load spell list<br>     Save spell list<br><br>So get a spell line up you like.  Load all the spells in the order you like and then right click on the book and save your spell list and choose a name.<br><br>Do this for a few different spell lineups you want to switch between.   This allows you to switch all 8 spells out at once to a whole new set and it happens automatically (not instantly, you still sit down, open up book and do each spell 1 at a time, but it all happens without you flipping around the pages of your book looking for the spell you want).<br><br>This also works if you want to unmemorize ALL of your spells and then load up 1 or more spells and save the shortened list.  Now, you have all 8 spells loaded with your main spells and then you can load up another spell list that has maybe just 2 spells and it will unload the spells for THOSE TWO gems and replace them with the spells in the newly loaded list and it WON'T unload all of the other ones!<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Kanador Dabreeze<br><br>58 Enchanter on The Rathe</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >2 Replies</td></tr></table>
